30 \u0428\u043c\u0438\u0433\u0430\u043b\u044f}}) is a [[government of Ukraine]] formed on 4 March 2020, and led by [[Denys Shmyhal]].<ref name=radaappointshmyh>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pravda.com.ua/news/2020/03/4/7242529/|title=\u0414\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0441 \u0428\u043c\u0438\u0433\u0430\u043b\u044c \u2013 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u043c'\u0454\u0440 \u0423\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0438|website=[[Ukrayinska Pravda]]|language=uk|access-date=2020-03-08}}</ref>\n\n== Appointment of Shmyhal as Prime Minister ==\nThe appointment of Shmyhal as the Prime Minister of Ukraine was approved by the [[Verkhovna Rada]] on 4 March 2020.<ref name=radaappointshmyh/> Shmyhal at the time of his appointment was an acting vice prime minister.<ref name=radaappointshmyh/> The 291 People's deputies voted for his candidacy, while the members of most of the other factions ([[Opposition Platform \u2014 For Life]], [[European Solidarity]], Fatherland, and Voice) did not support it.<ref name=radaappointshmyh/>\n\n{| align=\"left\" class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n! |Faction\n! |'''Yes'''<ref name=radavote>[http://w1.c1.rada.gov.ua/pls/radan_gs09/ns_golos?g_id=4315 \u041f\u043e\u0456\u043c\u0435\u043d\u043d\u0435 \u0433\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0432\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044f \u043f\u0440\u043e \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0435\u043a\u0442 \u041f\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438]. [[Verkhovna Rada]]. 4 March 2020</ref><ref>[https://www.slovoidilo.ua/2020/03/04/infografika/polityka/rada-pryznachyla-shmyhalya-premyerom-yak-holosuvaly-nardepy The Rada appoint Shmyhal a prime minister: how people's deputies were voting (\u0420\u0430\u0434\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0437\u043d\u0430\u0447\u0438\u043b\u0430 \u0428\u043c\u0438\u0433\u0430\u043b\u044f \u043f\u0440\u0435\u043c'\u0454\u0440\u043e\u043c: \u044f\u043a \u0433\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0432\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u043d\u0430\u0440\u0434\u0435\u043f\u0438)]. Slovoidilo. 4 March 2020</ref>\n! |No\n! |Abstained\n! |Did not vote\n! |Absent\n|-----\n| '''[[Servant of the People (political party)|Servant of the People]]'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#00B000;\" | '''242'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:red;color:white;\"| 0\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:yellow;\"| 1\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:purple;color:white;\"| 0\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#cccccc;\" | 5\n|-----\n| '''[[Opposition Platform \u2014 For Life]]'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#00B000;\" | '''0'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:red;color:white;\"| 35\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:yellow;\"| 2\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:purple;color:white;\"| 3\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#cccccc;\" | 4\n|-----\n| '''[[European Solidarity]]'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#00B000;\" | '''0'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:red;color:white;\"| 24\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:yellow;\"| 0\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:purple;color:white;\"| 1\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#cccccc;\" | 2\n|-----\n| '''[[All-Ukrainian Union \"Fatherland\"|Fatherland]]'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#00B000;\" | '''0'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:red;color:white;\"| 0\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:yellow;\"| 20\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:purple;color:white;\"| 1\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#cccccc;\" | 3\n|-----\n| '''For the Future'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#00B000;\" | '''18'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:red;color:white;\"| 0\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:yellow;\"| 0\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:purple;color:white;\"| 2\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#cccccc;\" | 2\n|-----\n| '''[[Voice (Ukrainian political party)|Voice]]'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#00B000;\" | '''0'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:red;color:white;\"| 0\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:yellow;\"| 19\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:purple;color:white;\"| 1\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#cccccc;\" | 0\n|-----\n| '''TRUST'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#00B000;\" | '''17'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:red;color:white;\"| 0\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:yellow;\"| 0\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:purple;color:white;\"| 0\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#cccccc;\" | 0\n|-----\n| Non-affiliated\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#00B000;\" | '''14'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:red;color:white;\"| 0\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:yellow;\"| 4\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:purple;color:white;\"| 1\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#cccccc;\" | 2\n|-----\n| '''All factions'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#00B000;\" | '''291'''\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:red;color:white;\"| 59\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:yellow;\"| 46\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:purple;color:white;\"| 9\n| style=\"text-align:center;background-color:#cccccc;\" | 18\n|+\n|}\n{{clear}}\n\nThe transition from the [[Honcharuk government]] was treated in some local press as worrisome.<ref name=\"btkp\">{{cite news |last1=Talant |first1=Bermet |title=Hasty government reshuffle sows disquiet at home, abroad |publisher=Kyiv Post |date=6 March 2020 |url=https://www.kyivpost.com/ukraine-politics/hasty-government-reshuffle-sows-disquiet-at-home-abroad.html}}</ref><ref name=\"oskp\">{{cite news |last1=Sorokin |first1=Oleksiy |title=Shmygal\u2019s awkward start as nation\u2019s prime minister |url=https://www.kyivpost.com/ukraine-politics/shmygals-awkward-start-as-nations-prime-minister.html |publisher=Kyiv Post |date=6 March 2020}}</ref> In his 4 March address to the Rada, President Zelenskyy hoped for a stronger government.<ref name=\"pukz\">{{cite news |last1=ZELENSKYY |first1=VOLODYMYR |title=Speech by President of Ukraine Volodymyr Zelenskyy at an extraordinary session of the Verkhovna Rada |url=https://www.president.gov.ua/en/news/vistup-prezidenta-ukrayini-volodimira-zelenskogo-na-pozacher-60017 |publisher=PRESIDENT OF UKRAINE Official website |date=4 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Composition==\n<onlyinclude>{| class=wikitable\n! rowspan= | Nominating<br>party key\n| style=\"background:{{Servant of the People (political party)/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[Servant of the People]]\n|-\n! rowspan= | Presidential nominations\n| style=\"background:blue\" |\n| [[Ukrainian President|President]] [[Volodymyr Zelensky]]\n|}\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|-\n!colspan=1 style=\"background-color:#ADD8E6\"|Logo\n!colspan=1 style=\"background-color:#ADD8E6\"|Office\n!colspan=2 style=\"background-color:#ADD8E6\"|Incumbent\n|-\n| \n| [[Prime Minister of Ukraine|Prime Minister]]\n| style= \"background: \"|\n| [[Denys Shmyhal]]\n|-\n| rowspan=4|\n| [[First Vice Prime Minister of Ukraine|Vice Prime Minister]] ([[Ukraine\u2013European Union relations|European integration]])\n| style=\"background: \" |\n| [[Vadym Prystaiko]]\n|-\n| [[First Vice Prime Minister of Ukraine|Vice Prime Minister]] \n| rowspan=2; style=\"background:{{Servant of the People (political party)/meta/color}}\" |\n| rowspan=2 | [[Mykhailo Fedorov]]{{efn|Fedorov is a non-partisan member of Ukrainian parliament and government.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20190829235635/https://www.cvk.gov.ua/pls/vnd2019/wp407pt001f01=919pf7201=18494 Mykhailo Fedorov]. Central Election Commission.</ref>}}\n|-\n| [[Ministry of Digital Transformation|Minister of 